favourite.article:
1. I'm just a little flower with open face; 
I'm fully turned to God, receiving grace.
I don’t know how to try. This is my case
I’m just a lily trusting God

2. There’s nothing on this earth that I desire. 
There’s no experience that I require.
I only want one thing that I aspire
To be a lily trusting God.

3. If when I trust in God I’m put to shame; 
If when I walk with God I come out lame;
These things don’t bother me; I’m not to blame
Since I’m a lily trusting God.

4. With all your worrying to clothe yourself; 
So many lies you’ve told to gather wealth;
And though you’ve gotten rich, you’ve lost your health
Just be a lily trusting God.

5. It seems you know so much, But yet you fall;
And though you talk so much, yet you won’t call;
So what’s the use of it, for after all
Just be a lily trusting God.

6. So please don’t bother me with all your fears; 
You strive and try so hard with sweat and tears.
Have faith in Jesus Christ. He’s always near! 
Just be a lily trusting God.

7. Yes, please don’t bother me, I’m growing fine. 
Oh please don’t share with me what’s on your mind.
I may not know so much, but still I shine. 
For I’m a lily trusting God.

8. And please don’t bother me with all your cares; 
Don’t make me listen to your begging prayers;
Our God is very great—He really cares! 
Just be a lily trusting God.

9. It seems that I don’t care so much for you; 
But if you knew my heart, I really do;
Yet lilies don’t know how to fret and stew
I’m just a lily, How ’bout you?
